From 3b880d6cf92eb007e23da7109c2b22f660046461 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 15:03:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?perf#24c2e:=20fix=20DCC2=20crash=20=E2=80=94=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?bypass=20prebinding=20shortcut=20in=20doRebase=20(#91=20SOLVED)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Root cause of the DCC2 2-dylib smoke crash: a substituted DCC2 image sets
fInSharedCache=true (in instantiateFromCache), which makes
ImageLoaderMachO::usablePrebinding() return true, so doRebase() takes the
"prebinding is valid, skip rebase" early-return BEFORE ever calling rebase().
The perf#24c2e DCC2 fixup guard lives in rebase()/doBind(), so it never fired:
the cache-native fixup table was NEVER applied, the images' DATA (GOT / bind
pointers) stayed unrelocated, and the first deref of a cached image's pointer
faulted (the ~0xdd near-null). This was NOT the "scattered LINKEDIT" theory —
the LINKEDIT/symtab math is self-consistent; construction succeeded for both
images (both "substituted cached image" lines print). The crash was deferred to
first use of unfixed DATA.

Fix: in ImageLoaderMachO::doRebase(), before the usablePrebinding() shortcut,
detect a DCC2 image (DCC2Reader::shared()->isDCC2Image(machHeader())) and route
straight to rebase(context, fSlide), which applies the whole-cache fixup table
once via DCC2Reader::applyAllFixupsOnce(). A DCC2 image is NOT prebound.

Verified by an instrumented live 2-dylib smoke ({libsystem_blocks, libunwind}):
both images substituted from the packed cache, doRebase bypasses prebinding for
each, rebase() fires with isDCC2=1, applyAllFixupsOnce applies all 55 fixups
(50 rebase + 5 bind) once for the whole cache with NO crash, and /usr/bin/true
runs to completion returning exit 0. No SIGSEGV/halt in dserver.log. Prod dyld
restored byte-identical (79b22273 both copies); instrumentation logs removed.
